  "prompt": "What is the procedure to file RTI?",
  "response": "Here's the procedure to file an RTI (Right to Information) application in India:\n\n1. Identify the public authority\n- Determine the specific government department or organization holding the required information\n\n2. Prepare the RTI application\n- Write in simple, clear language\n- Specify the information you want\n- Provide details precisely\n- Use the standard RTI application form\n\n3. Application submission methods\n- In person at the designated RTI office\n- By post/speed post\n- Online through the department's website\n- Through email (if facility available)\n\n4. Application details\n- Your full name\n- Complete address\n- Contact details\n- Information sought\n- Relevant supporting documents (if any)\n\n5. Pay application fee\n- Generally Rs. 10-50 depending on state\n- Can be paid via:\n  - Postal order\n  - Demand draft\n  - Cash\n  - Online payment\n\n6. Obtain acknowledgment\n- Get receipt/reference number\n- Keep proof of application submission\n\n7. Wait for response\n- Department must respond within 30 days\n- If no response, can file first appeal\n- Can approach Information Commission for second appeal\n\nNote: Applications can be rejected under specific exemption categories defined in the RTI Act.",
